INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '7c9594b8-910d-4f72-a3f8-18488735dc46',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$SolidJS Web Vitals — How Signals, Suspense, and lazy() Move Your LCP, CLS, and INP$escape$,
  $escape$SolidJS's fine-grained reactivity changes how each Web Vital behaves versus VDOM frameworks.

**LCP**: `lazy()` is a bundle-splitter — never wrap above-the-fold components with it. LCP content must live in the critical chunk. In SolidStart, pass `{ deferStream: true }` to `createResource` to block the SSR shell until the resource resolves, embedding data in the initial HTML rather than a streamed patch that arrives later.

**CLS**: `Suspense` fallbacks must physically reserve the space the resolved content will occupy — a zero-height skeleton causes a measurable shift. During refetch, reach for `resource.latest`: it returns the last successful value while `resource.loading` is `true`, preventing the collapse-and-reflow cycle that tanks CLS scores.

**INP**: Fine-grained reactivity is your baseline advantage — SolidJS patches only the DOM nodes subscribed to the changed signal, not an entire subtree. However, calling multiple `setSignal()` functions in one event handler schedules separate synchronous flushes. Wrap them in `batch()` to coalesce writes into a single DOM commit, minimising time-to-paint for that interaction.$escape$,
  $escape$import { createResource, createSignal, batch, Suspense } from "solid-js";

function ArticleFeed() {
  const [page, setPage] = createSignal(1);
  const [filter, setFilter] = createSignal("latest");

  // INP: one DOM flush instead of two
  const handleFilterChange = (f: string) =>
    batch(() => { setFilter(f); setPage(1); });

  // LCP: deferStream embeds data in the SSR shell
  const [articles] = createResource(
    () => ({ page: page(), filter: filter() }),
    fetchArticles,
    { deferStream: true }
  );

  return (
    // CLS: reserve space; use .latest to avoid refetch collapse
    <div style={{ "min-height": "480px" }}>
      <Suspense fallback={<FeedSkeleton />}>
        <ArticleList items={articles.latest ?? articles()} />
      </Suspense>
    </div>
  );
}$escape$,
  $escape$typescript$escape$,
